Greenwich Avenue (center to right margin) north side, east from W. 11th Street (left), showing the westerly portion of this triangular block that has Sixth Avenue for a base. The modern white building on the right is the new Womens Detention House. To the left is St. Vincents Hospital. View 2 eliminates this feature and uncloses the south side of W. 11th Street. Note the Sixth Avenue "E1" and its 8th Street Station in the background. The gas station at the right is at the S.E. corner of Seventh and Greenwich Avenues.
October 13, 1930
View 2: July 31, 1938
P. L. Sperr
858/B 2 Neg# 495
858/B 3 Neg# 496
